  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Humanitarian Activities in Afghanistan in Support of IOM Activities Assisting Refugee Returnees and Vulnerable Migrants Included in the IOM COVID Strategic Response and Recovery Plan (SRRP)</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This project will ensure the continuity of lifesaving essential health care, including critical COVID-19 responses, in Afghanistan, focusing on multiple displaced and mobile populations, including documented refugee returnees, as well as host communities. This will include strengthening coordination, providing essential health care, Risk Communication and Community Engagement (RCCE), and border-level surveillance, through continued deployment of seven mobile health teams and rapid response teams. Additionally, IOM will increase knowledge of population flows, returns, displacement and migration through the continued implementation of IOM&#x2019;s Displacement Tracking Matrix (DTM) to ensure better-targeted, evidence-based delivery of assistance to populations in most need in priority locations.</narrative>
  </description>
